In a speech at the White House, President Joe Biden thanked African Americans for their contributions to the country and highlighted the diversity within his administration. He acknowledged the presence of African Americans in high-ranking positions and recognized the importance of historically Black colleges and universities (HBCUs). Biden also discussed his administration's efforts to address issues such as COVID-19, economic relief, infrastructure, police and criminal justice reform, voting rights, and equity. He expressed optimism about the younger generation and their potential to create a more just and hopeful future. The President dismissed concerns about nuclear war when asked by reporters.